text: Skil Brum is a mountain in the Karakoram range, in Pakistan. Skil Brum is part of the Baltoro Muztagh subrange. It is the 65th highest mountain in the world. The first people to reach the top were Fritz Wintersteller and Marcus Schmuck, in 1957. == References == Category:Mountains of Gilgit-Baltistan Category:Karakoram
